      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for the info. the connection backlog idea is interesting. but it still feels so random... like, why just during peak times and why so intermittently? it's like some invisible thing is just cutting the wires right when we need them most. \n\nis there any chance it's a hardware glitch or something more \"random\" than just simple resource limits? like something deeper in the AWS infra that we can't see?",
      "source": "evaluator"
